The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks, suggesting that it could also belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

Furthermore, the paper analyzes the contraction and separation properties of the network, which could fall under the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

The paper's focus on the performance of deep networks and the analysis of local support vectors could also suggest that it belongs to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Finally, the paper's use of TensorFlow, a popular deep learning framework, could suggest that it belongs to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language), which includes topics related to natural language processing and machine learning.
